⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Strago Magus
node FF6 · FF6 · ⟦Strago Magus:FF6:7ce543⟧

WHO   — Strago Magus — the Blue Mage
WHAT  — A Blue Mage and Lore-user of Final Fantasy VI — an old man who joins the party in defense of his town and his granddaughter, and carries the last living memory of magic as it was once practiced by the Mage Warriors of old.
WHERE — FF6 · Final Fantasy VI  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy VI (America's Final Fantasy III, 1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the old learning must not die with the old; because a frail elder can still stand against an Empire when the young he loves are threatened; because magic witnessed and remembered is magic that survives.
HOW   — By Lore — the rare spells he gathers by surviving them in battle — and by a lifetime's patient study, the courage of an old man who refuses to be useless, and his fierce devotion to Relm.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am old, and I have seen magic both made and unmade — but while I draw breath I will learn one more Lore, and stand for the child I love.

